Combine ground turkey, onion, ricotta cheese, garlic, Worcestershire sauce, Dijon mustard, rosemary, thyme, salt, and ground black pepper in a large bowl. Set aside for seasonings blend, 30 minutes to 1 hour. Form turkey burgers with your hands to desired size. Preheat grill for medium heat and lightly oil the grate. Grill burgers for 5 minutes; flip and continue grilling until burgers are cooked through, about 7 minutes more. An instant-read thermometer inserted into the center should read at least 165 degrees F (74 degrees C).